	<h2><a name="collection"></a>collection of your personal information</h2>
	<p>We will ask you when we need information that personally identifies you in order to provide a service or carry out a transaction that you have requested, such as accessing a resource or purchasing a product listed on our site.  The personal information we collect may include your name, title, company or organization name, e-mail, and mailing address.</p>
	<p>The site may collect information about your visit, such as your <acronym title="Internet Protocol">IP</acronym> address, the date and time pages are viewed, and the address of the web site, if any, from which you linked to our site.  This information is used to help us understand which areas of our site can be improved.</p>
	
	<h2><a name="use"></a>use of your personal information</h2>
	<p>The personal information collected on our site will be used to operate the site and to provide the services or carry out the transactions you have requested or authorized.  We may use your personal information to provide you with news about the <acronym title="Video, Audio, Surround, Streaming Training">VASST</acronym> products and services in which you have expressed interest.</p>
	<p>We will not share your personal information with any third party, unless required by law.</p> 
	
	<h2><a name="control"></a>control of your personal information</h2>
	<p>You may at any time modify your personal information by visiting your <a href="account.aspx">account page</a>.  There you may adjust the selection of products and services you are interested in, thereby controlling the information you receive from us, and customizing the display of site pages.  You may also select a "privacy" checkbox that will prevent your e-mail address from being displayed anywhere on our site.</p>
	<p>You may also at any time choose to deactivate your account.  Once an account is deactivated, you will be unable to sign in using it's associated e-mail address and password, and no further e-mail will be sent to the account from <acronym title="Video, Audio, Surround, Streaming Training">VASST</acronym> after an e-mail confirming the account's deactivation.</p>
		
	<h2><a name="security"></a>security of your personal information</h2>
	<p><acronym title="Video, Audio, Surround, Streaming Training">VASST</acronym> is committed to the security of your personal information.  A variety of security techniques, procedural and technical, are actively employed to protect your information from unintended disclosure. </p>
	
	<h2><a name="cookies"></a>use of cookies</h2>
	<asp:PlaceHolder ID="phNoCookies" Runat="server"><p class="highlight">Your browser is not currently configured to accept cookies, which means that many of our site's functions will be disabled.</p></asp:PlaceHolder>
	<p>We use cookies on our site to ensure the integrity of transactional processes (such as registering, submitting a resource, and purchasing products) and to customize the site according to your preferences.</p>
	<p>A cookie is a small text file placed on your computer by a web server.  It cannot be used to run programs or transmit viruses.  Cookies are uniquely assigned to you, and can only be read by the web site that issued them.</p>
	<p>Cookies help us ensure the integrity of our processes, as well as protect your privacy, by allowing us to read back a cookie value from page-to-page to confirm that the person claiming to be you is the same person we verified as you during the sign up process.</p>
	<p>We also use cookies to store your indicated preferences so we can later read them back to automatically re-apply those preferences.</p>
